<ContentLayout title="What Is a Home Warranty?" description="A home warranty is a service contract that may help with covered repairs to listed home systems and appliances." seoTitle="What Is a Home Warranty? | Best Home Warranty Near Me" seoDescription="Learn how home warranties work, what they may cover, what they usually exclude, and how to compare plans without getting weird about it." eyebrow="Home warranty basics">
<h2>The plain-English version</h2><p>A home warranty is not homeowners insurance. It is a service contract. It may help pay for covered repair or replacement when listed systems or appliances break from normal wear and tear.</p><h2>Check availability before the sales pitch gets loud</h2><p>Start with your ZIP code. If you are in Iowa or Illinois, we can help you compare coverage options now. If not, we will keep you posted when we expand.</p><LeadCaptureGate /><h2>Read the fine print before buying</h2><p>Check coverage limits, exclusions, service call fees, waiting periods, and contractor rules. Some plans are useful. Some are expensive disappointment subscriptions.</p><h2>Start with likely breakdowns</h2><p>Older HVAC, plumbing, water heaters, and kitchen appliances deserve special attention. If the contract is vague there, keep comparing.</p>
</ContentLayout>
